<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1236090951">.mw-parser-output .hatnote{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output div.hatnote{padding-left:1.6em;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .hatnote i{font-style:normal}.mw-parser-output .hatnote+link+.hatnote{margin-top:-0.5em}@media print{body.ns-0 .mw-parser-output .hatnote{display:none!important}}</style><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article is about a generalized derivative of a multivariate function. For another use in mathematics, see <a href="/wiki/Slope" title="Slope">Slope</a>. For a similarly spelled unit of angle, see <a href="/wiki/Gradian" title="Gradian">Gradian</a>. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Gradient_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Gradient (disambiguation)">Gradient (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
