    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \nabla f(\rho ,\varphi ,z)={\frac {\partial f}{\partial \rho }}\mathbf {e} _{\rho }+{\frac {1}{\rho }}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial \varphi }}\mathbf {e} _{\varphi }+{\frac {\partial f}{\partial z}}\mathbf {e} _{z},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0bb569d0b33fee08a15753941010b4e7284b83a2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:39.972ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \nabla f(\rho ,\varphi ,z)={\frac {\partial f}{\partial \rho }}\mathbf {e} _{\rho }+{\frac {1}{\rho }}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial \varphi }}\mathbf {e} _{\varphi }+{\frac {\partial f}{\partial z}}\mathbf {e} _{z},}"></span>
</p><p>where <span class="texhtml"><i>ρ</i></span> is the axial distance, <span class="texhtml"><i>φ</i></span> is the azimuthal or azimuth angle, <span class="texhtml"><i>z</i></span> is the axial coordinate, and <span class="texhtml"><b>e</b><sub><i>ρ</i></sub></span>, <span class="texhtml"><b>e</b><sub><i>φ</i></sub></span> and <span class="texhtml"><b>e</b><sub><i>z</i></sub></span> are unit vectors pointing along the coordinate directions.
</p><p>In <a href="/wiki/Spherical_coordinate_system#Definition" title="Spherical coordinate system">spherical coordinates</a> with a Euclidean metric, the gradient is given by:<sup id="cite_ref-Schey-1992_10-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Schey-1992-10"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \nabla f(r,\theta ,\varphi )={\frac {\partial f}{\partial r}}\mathbf {e} _{r}+{\frac {1}{r}}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial \theta }}\mathbf {e} _{\theta }+{\frac {1}{r\sin \theta }}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial \varphi }}\mathbf {e} _{\varphi },}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
