        <mo>=</mo>
        <munderover>
          <mo>∑<!-- ∑ --></mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mo>=</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
              <mi>f</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>i</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <msub>
              <mi>h</mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>i</mi>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <msup>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mover>
                <mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi>
                <mo mathvariant="bold" stretchy="false">^<!-- ^ --></mo>
              </mover>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\textstyle \mathrm {d} f=\sum _{i=1}^{n}\,{\frac {\partial f}{\partial x^{i}}}{\frac {1}{h_{i}}}\mathbf {\hat {e}} ^{i}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/da2437bfcc3e0da20de6e7694195cafa0580f9fd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.671ex; width:19.675ex; height:4.509ex;" alt="{\textstyle \mathrm {d} f=\sum _{i=1}^{n}\,{\frac {\partial f}{\partial x^{i}}}{\frac {1}{h_{i}}}\mathbf {\hat {e}} ^{i}}"></span>),
</p><p>where we cannot use Einstein notation, since it is impossible to avoid the repetition of more than two indices. Despite the use of upper and lower indices, <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {\hat {e}} _{i}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mover>
                <mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi>
                <mo mathvariant="bold" stretchy="false">^<!-- ^ --></mo>
              </mover>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {\hat {e}} _{i}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f01cfee86a741d3d25c6510aea329ab584019060" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.136ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {\hat {e}} _{i}}"></span>, <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {\hat {e}} ^{i}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msup>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mover>
                <mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi>
                <mo mathvariant="bold" stretchy="false">^<!-- ^ --></mo>
              </mover>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {\hat {e}} ^{i}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/69a1e1ef2476e6b38b316009b5f386ceb8e9d238" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.136ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {\hat {e}} ^{i}}"></span>, and <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle h_{i}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>h</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle h_{i}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d535f210cbd9b9fe6689e61427b3e213e5b2d547" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.139ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle h_{i}}"></span> are neither contravariant nor covariant.
</p><p>The latter expression evaluates to the expressions given above for cylindrical and spherical coordinates.
</p>
