    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \nabla ^{a}f^{b}=g^{ac}\nabla _{c}f^{b},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/321ccec9b721069aa6171a25e1070dbe4b86378c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:17.111ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \nabla ^{a}f^{b}=g^{ac}\nabla _{c}f^{b},}"></span>
</p><p>where <span class="texhtml">∇<sub><i>c</i></sub></span> is the connection.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Riemannian_manifolds">Riemannian manifolds</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gradient&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Riemannian manifolds"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>For any <a href="/wiki/Smooth_function" class="mw-redirect" title="Smooth function">smooth function</a> <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">f</span> on a Riemannian manifold <span class="texhtml">(<i>M</i>, <i>g</i>)</span>, the gradient of <span class="texhtml"><i>f</i></span> is the vector field <span class="texhtml">∇<i>f</i></span> such that for any vector field <span class="texhtml"><i>X</i></span>,
<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle g(\nabla f,X)=\partial _{X}f,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>g</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">∇<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>X</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>X</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle g(\nabla f,X)=\partial _{X}f,}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/016ba65c6ad393de95fce69303333e29fc5368b5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.044ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle g(\nabla f,X)=\partial _{X}f,}"></span>
that is,
<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle g_{x}{\big (}(\nabla f)_{x},X_{x}{\big )}=(\partial _{X}f)(x),}">
