          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
              <msub>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>j</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo>∘<!-- ∘ --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>φ<!-- φ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mo maxsize="2.470em" minsize="2.470em">|</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>φ<!-- φ --></mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
            <mi>x</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \sum _{j=1}^{n}X^{j}{\big (}\varphi (x){\big )}{\frac {\partial }{\partial x_{j}}}(f\circ \varphi ^{-1}){\Bigg |}_{\varphi (x)},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/78dcb98b7081519ff2d497a76f8918a2934de446" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.338ex; width:31.787ex; height:7.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \sum _{j=1}^{n}X^{j}{\big (}\varphi (x){\big )}{\frac {\partial }{\partial x_{j}}}(f\circ \varphi ^{-1}){\Bigg |}_{\varphi (x)},}"></span>
where <span class="texhtml"><i>X</i><span style="padding-left:0.12em;"><sup><i>j</i></sup></span></span> denotes the <span class="texhtml"><i>j</i></span>th component of <span class="texhtml"><i>X</i></span> in this coordinate chart.
</p><p>So, the local form of the gradient takes the form:
</p><p><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \nabla f=g^{ik}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial x^{k}}}{\textbf {e}}_{i}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi mathvariant="normal">∇<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>g</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
              <mi>f</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
              <msup>
                <mi>x</mi>
                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>k</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msup>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext mathvariant="bold">e</mtext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \nabla f=g^{ik}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial x^{k}}}{\textbf {e}}_{i}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/da3f6be5bfdc620a2910ae011dae491d5d5e73a8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:16.332ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \nabla f=g^{ik}{\frac {\partial f}{\partial x^{k}}}{\textbf {e}}_{i}.}"></span>
</p><p>Generalizing the case <span class="texhtml"><i>M</i> = <b>R</b><sup><i>n</i></sup></span>, the gradient of a function is related to its exterior derivative, since
<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle (\partial _{X}f)(x)=(df)_{x}(X_{x}).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>X</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <msub>
          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>X</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle (\partial _{X}f)(x)=(df)_{x}(X_{x}).}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3d03472524b7b7bb39f84e867a2e7f2fe29fa405" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.221ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle (\partial _{X}f)(x)=(df)_{x}(X_{x}).}"></span>
More precisely, the gradient <span class="texhtml">∇<i>f</i></span> is the vector field associated to the differential 1-form <span class="texhtml"><i>df</i></span> using the <a href="/wiki/Musical_isomorphism" title="Musical isomorphism">musical isomorphism</a>
<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \sharp =\sharp ^{g}\colon T^{*}M\to TM}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi mathvariant="normal">♯<!-- ♯ --></mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">♯<!-- ♯ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>g</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>:<!-- : --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>T</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>∗<!-- ∗ --></mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mi>M</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">→<!-- → --></mo>
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \sharp =\sharp ^{g}\colon T^{*}M\to TM}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/37af56f4726d43f9423825c41e5df20927250f1b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:19.872ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \sharp =\sharp ^{g}\colon T^{*}M\to TM}"></span>
(called "sharp") defined by the metric <span class="texhtml"><i>g</i></span>. The relation between the exterior derivative and the gradient of a function on <span class="texhtml"><b>R</b><sup><i>n</i></sup></span> is a special case of this in which the metric is the flat metric given by the dot product.
</p>
